headline: CHRW Q1 Earnings Call: Margin Expansion and Productivity Offset Lower Revenue in Tough Freight Market
summary: Freight transportation intermediary C.H. Robinson (NASDAQ:CHRW) missed Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025, with sales falling 8.3% year on year to $4.05 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.17 per share was 11.4% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
